# TypeScript

- **Strict** mode (`tsconfig.json`); no `any` unless unavoidable
- Imports: prefer `@/` alias over deep relative paths
- Node built-ins in server code: `import { createHmac } from 'node:crypto'`

## Style (match surrounding file)

- Some files use semicolons and double quotes (`app/page.tsx`), others omit semicolons and use single quotes (`proxy.ts`, `lib/auth.ts`) — **do not reformat entire files** when making small edits
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes used in libs; inline props types are fine for small components

## Server-only modules

- `lib/auth.ts`, `lib/rate-limit.ts`, `app/actions/auth.ts` — only import from Server Components, Server Actions, Route Handlers, or `proxy.ts`
- Do not import `lib/auth` session helpers into client components (use server actions or API instead)

## Types from libraries

- AI SDK: use package exports (`UIMessage`, hook return types) rather than duplicating message shapes
- Next.js: `NextRequest`, `NextResponse`, `Metadata` from `next` packages
